      <arrangement id="aspace_eeb708648783f559dd4e2d89e8fca2cc">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>This collection is organized into two series: I: Wright family, 1817 - 1889. II: Robinson, Joseph Johnson, 1814 - 1907.</p>
      </arrangement>
      <bioghist id="aspace_87c4cd51b710cdaceb72a95608de1cf0">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Richard Wright was born in Liverpool, England, in 1794, the son of John Wright, a Unitarian lay preacher. Seeking to escape religious persecution, the Wright family emigrated from Liverpool to Georgetown, Washington in 1817. The family corresponded with Peter Robinson and others in Liverpool; their letters contain impressions of Georgetown, Washington, D. C., and Alexandria, Virginia, as well as extensive writing about their Abolistionist views. Richard Wright died in 1870.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <prefercite id="aspace_10cc85080e32eb8628c2ac912fee7606">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Wright Family Papers. General Collection, Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_bbbee31ff569060807450afccbf2ec6d">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Collections are processed to a variety of levels, depending on the work necessary to make them usable, their perceived research value, the availability of staff, competing priorities, and whether or not further accruals are expected.  The library attempts to provide a basic level of preservation and access for all collections, and does more extensive processing of higher priority collections as time and resources permit.</p>
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_69377f00d4e5498b0733d90b2fd49fcf">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection contains correspondence between Richard Wright and Hannah Wright and Peter Robinson, with related correspondence between members of the Robinson family and others. It also includes writings by Richard Wright, as well as correspondence and legal documents relating to Joseph Johnson Robinson.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      <userestrict id="aspace_7add620f64cfbc3bf0effbdc366ef89a">
         <head>Conditions Governing Use</head>
         <p>The Wright Family Papers are the physical property of the Beinecke Rare Book and Manuscript Library, Yale University. Literary rights, including copyright, belong to the authors or their legal heris and assigns. For further information consult the appropriate curator.</p>
      </userestrict>
